g.text: To conclude, the surprising variability in preservation quality of insects in amber means that
to read this fossil treasure trove correctly, using it to investigate terrestrial ecosystems and
insect evolution, we must understand the biases that operate in creating such fossils. Here we
show that decay experiments provide a useful platformwith which to investigate bias between
different aspects of the amber fossil record.
